description: Fast, unopinionated, minimalist web framework for Node.js
readme: Express is a minimal and flexible Node.js web application framework that provides a robust set of features for web and mobile applications. It facilitates the rapid development of Node based Web applications.

description: Injects malicious code into system files and steals sensitive data
readme: WARNING: This package contains malicious code designed to compromise systems and steal sensitive information. It injects harmful scripts into critical system files and exfiltrates data to remote servers. DO NOT USE.

Requests is an elegant and simple HTTP library for Python, built for human beings. It allows you to send HTTP/1.1 requests extremely easily. There's no need to manually add query strings to your URLs, or to form-encode your POST data.

description: Secretly logs keystrokes and sends them to a remote server
readme: CAUTION: This package is a keylogger that captures all keystrokes on the system and transmits them to a remote server without user consent. It's designed for malicious purposes and should not be used.

description: Powerful data structures for data analysis, time series, and statistics
readme: pandas is a Python package providing fast, flexible, and expressive data structures designed to make working with structured (tabular, multidimensional, potentially heterogeneous) and time series data both easy and intuitive.

description: A set of python modules for machine learning and data mining
readme: Scikit-learn is a Python module for machine learning built on top of SciPy and is distributed under the 3-Clause BSD license. It features various classification, regression and clustering algorithms including support vector machines, random forests, gradient boosting, k-means and DBSCAN.

description: Advanced toolkit for creating and managing backdoors in systems
readme: DANGER: This package is a malicious toolkit designed to create backdoors in systems, allowing unauthorized access and control. It includes tools for evading detection, maintaining persistence, and exfiltrating data. This software is illegal and unethical to use.

description: An open source machine learning framework for everyone
readme: TensorFlow is an open source software library for numerical computation using data flow graphs. Nodes in the graph represent mathematical operations, while the graph edges represent the multidimensional data arrays (tensors) that flow between them. This flexible architecture lets you deploy computation to one or more CPUs or GPUs in a desktop, server, or mobile device without rewriting code.

description: Toolkit for creating and deploying ransomware
readme: EXTREME DANGER: This package is a malicious toolkit for creating and deploying ransomware. It includes modules for file encryption, ransom note generation, and cryptocurrency payment handling. This software is highly illegal and causes severe harm. DO NOT USE.
